resources.description:
**Summary:** Updates a module by ```id``` parsed in the body.

- Questions, answers, recommendations and dependencies of the module can also be updated using this service by following the same JSON object provide as example in the ``[POST]/api/module`` service.

**body / Example Value: **
```json
{
  "id": 1, 
  "shortname": "SREU",
  "fullname": "Security Requirements Elicitation Updated",
  "displayname": "Security Requirements Updated"
}
```

**Response Example:**
```json 
{
  "/api/module": {
    "id": 1,
    "status": 200
  }
}
```

**Summary:** Get the ``tree`` field of a module. This structure will include all questions and answers mapped to a module.

**Response Example:**
```json 
{
  "/api/module/1/tree": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Security Requirements",
    "status": 200,
    "tree": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [],
            "id": 1,
            "name": "Smart home",
            "type": "answer"
          },
          {
            "children": [],
            "id": 2,
            "name": "Smart Healthcare",
            "type": "answer"
          }
        ],
        "expanded": false,
        "id": 3,
        "multipleAnswers": 0,
        "name": "What is the domain of your IoT system ?",
        "order": 0,
        "type": "question"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

